node.text: Spooky season is upon us 💀. To celebrate @thehaunting of Bly Manor, now streaming, only on Netflix, I created an Elizabethan makeup look inspired by the show as well as a dark, ghostly look inspired by one of Bly Manor’s most notorious hauntings – the Lady of the Lake. I also talked all about the terrifying truth of Bly Manor’s hauntings and so much more! The full video is up now on YouTube.com/LoeyLane. #ad

node.title: The Terrifying Truth of the Haunting of Bly Manor

node.text:
Three months at home 🔑🏡
My house is 94 this year. As I was knees deep in cleaning, per my usual Sunday routine, I couldn’t help but feel so nostalgic thinking over the last three months here. Living on my own for the first time ever, in the city of my dreams has been wildly exciting and terrifying and every mix of emotions in between. And this house, my home, is the cornerstone of it all.
I think that if my house’s walls could speak of all that she feels after standing for nearly 100 years, she would sing. She is timelessly beautiful, magnetic and warm. A fresh coat of paint was applied before I even moved in, yet it could never hide the history behind these walls. The stories of the children and families and puppies and frat boys who lived here before. And now, it provides a home to me.
Everyone thought I was crazy, moving into a home I had seen only once over FaceTime, from over 2,000 miles away. They couldn’t see what I felt deep in my bones, a resounding “yes” that I couldn’t keep from spilling out of my mouth within moments of seeing it. Weeks later when I walked through these doors for the first time, I immediately started to cry. Not out of disappointment or even joy, but from relief. Something deep within me recognized this house like an old friend. And I like to think she smiled back as I wept on those bare floors three months ago and said, “Welcome home. I’ve been waiting for you.”
What a blessing, what a joy it is to live in this house. Thank you for protecting my furry little flock and I. Thank you for your lessons and patience as I navigate life within your walls. Thank you for teaching me how to be okay by myself. My love for you, my beautiful, mischievous and strong home, is endless. 💓
